 bring the tiny guatemalan town up to western medical standards stanford daily guatemala's wise doctor pablo search chp search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest stanford students bring healthcare to rural poor in guatemala fsi stanford chp pcor in the news stanford report on june 30 2010 in video core faculty paul wise discusses his field work in guatemala in the news stanford school of medicine on january 4 2010 wise comments on california's pediatric care in the news los angeles times on january 25 2009 chp pcor researcher's other classroom is in guatemala april 1 2006 news in news article wise discusses debate among doctors on treating very premature infants march 22 2006 in the news article highlights wise's work providing care medical education in guatemala january 27 2006 in the news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 736 0815 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
